			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold">Calculating Child of Ro's Hitpoints When Focused With Summoner's Boon:</span>
<br />
The method is simple. Equip an item augmented with a Diamond Prism of Companionship. Summon a Child of Ro and immediately cast Elemental Draw, which maintains a fixed hitpoint drain of 800 points. Chart the hitpoint percentage lost, and extrapolate total hitpoints.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Results:</span>
<br />
800hp was 34% of Child of Ro's hitpoint total, with no shielding. Doing the proper mathematics:
<br />

<br />
1. (x)(34)=(100)(800)
<br />
2. 34x=(100)(800)
<br />
3. 34x=80000
<br />
4. 34x/34=x
<br />
5. 80000/34 = 2352.94
<br />
6. x = 2352.94
<br />

<br />
We arrive on the final value of <span style="font-weight: bold">2352.94 hitpoints.</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Problems:</span>
<br />
The unfocused hitpoints is listed at 2400. To recalculate this, we unequip the item with Summoner's Boon, and do the same summon + Elemental Draw test. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Results:</span>
<br />
This test, again with a fixed 800 hitpoint draw, displayed a 36% loss in hitpoints. Again doing the proper mathematics:
<br />

<br />
1. (x)(36)=(100)(800)
<br />
2. 36x=(100)(800)
<br />
3. 36x=80000
<br />
4. 36x/36=x
<br />
5. 80000/36 = 2222.22
<br />
6. x = 2222.22
<br />

<br />
We arrive on the total value of <span style="font-weight: bold">2222.22 hitpoints.</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: normal"><span style="font-weight: bold">Final Hitpoint Tally</span></span>
<br />
1. Unfocused: 2222HP
<br />
2. Summoner's Boon: 2353HP<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Warlock Ghrall</span>
